## **Types of Neural Networks**

- **Feedforward Neural Networks (FFNNs)** - Basic architecture, good for tabular data
- **Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs)** - Specialized for image processing
- **Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs/LSTMs)** - Handle sequential data like text or time series
- **Transformers** - State-of-the-art for NLP tasks

## **Key Advantages**
- Can learn complex non-linear patterns
- Excellent for unstructured data (images, text, audio)
- Flexible and can be applied to many domains

